link.n.01.defn: the means of connection between things linked in series

expl: the walls are held together with metal links placed in the wet mortar during construction
link.n.02.defn: a fastener that serves to join or connect

expl: the connection between church and state is inescapable

link.n.05.defn: a unit of length equal to 1/100 of a chain

link.n.06.defn: (computing) an instruction that connects one part of a program or an element on a list to another program or list

expl: he provided a liaison with the guerrillas
liaison.n.02.defn: a channel for communication between groups

radio_link.n.01.defn: a two-way radio communication system (usually microwave); part of a more extensive telecommunication network

link.n.09.defn: an interconnecting circuit between two or more locations for the purpose of transmitting and receiving data
